value: Wooden model of a rowing boat with seven oarsmen (one missing at the front); a look-out on the prow; and a stroke caller (cox) in the bow. He sits beside a rudder-oar. The figures have white painted kilts and red-brown flesh. Some figures have real linen loin cloths.
Tomb of Khety (Beni Hasan) early dynasty XII middle kingdom

summary_title: Burial customs of ancient Egypt; as illustrated by tombs of the Middle Kingdom, being a report of excavations made in the necropolis of Beni Hasan during 1902-4
Pharaohs and mortals; Egyptian art in the Middle Kingdom
Death on the Nile: Uncovering the Afterlife of Ancient Egypt
